or palette reuses .message.error values for system consistency\n- .message uses animation: fade-in 0.25s ease-out both — @keyframes fade-in defined in styles.css; fill-mode `both` ensures opacity:0 pre-start and opacity:1 post-end; translateY(4px)→0 adds subtle depth\n- .char-counter uses classList.toggle('warning', len >= threshold) on wrapper div — warning class at 80% of CHAR_LIMIT (6400/8000); updateCharCounter() called on input event and after submit clears chatInput\n- .output-box uses modifier classes .error (red: #fef3f2/#f9d3d0/--danger) and .exit-error (amber: #fffbf0/#fde8bb/--warning) — always classList.remove() both classes before each exec run to reset state; toggle .error on stderrOutput when stderr non-empty; toggle .exit-error on exitCodeOutput when exitCode !== 0\n- CSS breakpoints: 900px collapses .dashboard-grid + .form-grid to 1fr; 600px mobile breakpoint adds flex-wrap on .app-header, collapses .exec-form to 1fr, reduces .panel/.sub-panel padding (14px→10px), .app-shell padding (20px→12px), .chat-messages max-height (62vh→50vh); .status gets max-width+text-overflow:ellipsis at 600px to prevent header overflow\n\nUPDATED: 2026-03-23\n","numLines":35,"startLine":1,"totalLines":35}}}
