{"type":"assistant","message":{"content":[{"text":"F-031 is complete and committed. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**F-031: Web Dark Mode Support** — committed as `2f4e204`\n\n**Changes made to `public/styles.css`:**\n- Updated `:root { color-scheme: light dark }` — signals browser to render system UI in matching scheme\n- Added `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` block with:\n  - Full CSS variable palette override (9 variables with dark-optimized values)\n  - Hardcoded `#fff` overrides for `input`, `textarea`, `.chat-messages`, `.output-box`, `.screenshot-image` → `var(--panel)`\n  - Dedicated dark overrides for all modifier classes: `.status.connected` (deep green), `.status.error`/`.message.error`/`.output-box.error` (deep red `#450a0a`), `.output-box.exit-error` (deep amber `#431407`)\n\nThe solution is purely CSS — no JS, no backend changes. The UI automatically switches with the OS theme and reverts when the user switches back to light mode.","type":"text"}],"id":"req_vrtx_011CZK58HG5Gb4V67jkrwkaK","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":745,"output_tokens":1,"cache_read_input_tokens":61049},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"02647752-89ac-43ca-960e-cb2bd5f204c0","uuid":"8fdf74c9-d202-4bc4-9539-2d703210519c"}
